@startuml AdriaBOX_Upload_Sequence
!theme plain
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center

title AdriaBOX - File Upload Sequence (Zoom Level 1)

actor "Client (CLI)" as client
participant "Metadata Server" as server
database "SQLite DB" as db
participant "Storage Node A" as nodeA
participant "Storage Node B" as nodeB

client -> client : 1. Split file into chunks (e.g., 1MB each)

== Metadata Phase (REST API) ==

client -> server : 2. POST /api/upload (filename, num_chunks)
activate server

server -> db : 3. Check available nodes & allocate
activate db
db --> server : 4. Allocation Map (Chunk1->NodeA, Chunk2->NodeB)
deactivate db

server --> client : 5. 200 OK (Returns Allocation Map)
deactivate server

== Data Transfer Phase (TCP Sockets) ==

client -> nodeA : 6. TCP Connect & Send Chunk 1 (Binary Data)
activate nodeA
nodeA -> nodeA : 7. Write to Docker Volume
nodeA --> client : 8. TCP ACK (Chunk 1 saved)
deactivate nodeA

client -> nodeB : 9. TCP Connect & Send Chunk 2 (Binary Data)
activate nodeB
nodeB -> nodeB : 10. Write to Docker Volume
nodeB --> client : 11. TCP ACK (Chunk 2 saved)
deactivate nodeB

== Finalization ==

client -> server : 12. POST /api/upload/complete (filename)
activate server
server -> db : 13. Update index (Mark file as AVAILABLE)
server --> client : 14. 200 OK (Upload Successful)
deactivate server

@enduml

